All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<CourseWeekAvail>, java.util.Collection<CourseWeekAvail>, java.util.List<CourseWeekAvail>, java.util.RandomAccess
public class CourseAvailList
extends java.util.Vector<CourseWeekAvail>
implements java.io.Serializable

Used to keep track of multiple "WeekAvail" objects. Provides methods to check availability across multiple WeekAvails, book times, and add more WeekAvails. Written primarily to make it easy to obey NoClassOverlap preferences, as a course listed in multiple NCO's would need multiple WeekAvail objects.

Author:
Eric Liebowitz

Books a given time range on a given day for all NcoWeekAvail objects in this object.

Parameters:
c - The course to be booked
s - The start time
e - The end time
d - The day to book on
Returns:
